name: Siliciclastic Rock
description: Rocks primarily composed of silicate minerals and fragments derived from other rocks, especially by weathering and erosion.

name: Lithological unit
description: A body of rock characterized by a relatively uniform lithology, i.e., by its rock type.

name: Oil + Mudstone + Porous Rock
description: This seems to be a grouping of elements for some specific context. Without further information, it's difficult to assign a single stereotype.

name: Accumulation
description: The process of oil and gas gathering in a trap within the Earth's subsurface.

name: Hidrocarbon
description: Organic compounds consisting entirely of hydrogen and carbon; often refers to petroleum and natural gas.

name: Migration
description: The movement of hydrocarbons from their source rock to a reservoir or trap.

name: Granulometry
description: The study of the size distribution of particles in a material, such as sand or sediment, important for characterizing rocks.

name: Rock
description: A naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals.

name: Value
description: The economic worth of a resource like oil.

name: Oil + Porous rock
description: Similar to 'Oil + Mudstone...', needs context to determine a meaningful single stereotype.

name: Sandstone
description: A clastic sedimentary rock composed mainly of sand-sized mineral particles.

name: LithologicUnit qua sandstone
description: A lithologic unit specifically composed of sandstone. 'Qua' suggests a role or view of the unit.

name: Structure
description: The arrangement of and relations between parts or elements of a rock body, such as folds or faults, influencing hydrocarbon trapping.

name: Shale
description: A fine-grained clastic sedimentary rock formed from mud, often rich in organic matter (potential source rock).

name: Reservoir
description: A subsurface rock formation that contains hydrocarbons, characterized by porosity and permeability.

name: Oil
description: A liquid fossil fuel formed from the remains of ancient marine organisms.

name: contact
description: The surface or zone where two different rock units meet.

name: Generation
description: The process of hydrocarbons forming from organic matter in source rocks under heat and pressure.

name: Dimensions
description: The physical measurements of a rock unit, like length, width, and thickness.

name: Source Rock
description: A rock with abundant organic matter that, under heat and pressure, generates hydrocarbons.

name: Boundary Type
description: Classification of the nature of a boundary between rock units, e.g., sharp, gradational.

name: Trap
description: A geological structure that stops the upward migration of hydrocarbons, allowing them to accumulate.

name: LithologicUnit qua shale
description: A lithologic unit specifically made of shale. Again, 'qua' implies a role or specific perspective.

name: Porosity
description: The percentage of void space in a rock, critical for holding fluids like oil.

name: Oil + Trap
description: Lacks context for a single stereotype. May represent a relation (oil contained in a trap).

name: Seal
description: An impermeable rock layer that prevents hydrocarbons from escaping a trap.

name: Pre-generation
description: Refers to the state or conditions before the generation of hydrocarbons.

name: Quantity Organic matter
description: The amount of organic material present, crucial for source rock potential.

name: Boundary
description: The interface separating different rock units.

name: Nacionalidade Brasileira
description: A legal status that signifies a person is a citizen of Brazil.

name: Nacionalidade brasileira nata
description: Brazilian nationality acquired by birthright, typically granted to individuals born within Brazilian territory or to those born abroad to Brazilian parents.

name: Nacionalidade brasileira naturalizada
description: Brazilian nationality acquired through a legal process of naturalization, typically granted to individuals who meet specific requirements and demonstrate a connection to Brazil.

name: Estrangeiros de qualquer nacionalidade
description: Individuals who hold citizenship in a country other than Brazil.

name: A requerimento (art. 12,I,c, segunda parte)
description: Acquisition of Brazilian nationality based on a formal request and adherence to specific legal provisions outlined in Article 12, Section I, Subsection c, Second Part, of the Brazilian Nationality Law.

name: Registro no exterior (art. 12,I,c, primeira parte)
description: Acquisition of Brazilian nationality through registration at a Brazilian consulate abroad, as stipulated in Article 12, Section I, Subsection c, First Part, of the Brazilian Nationality Law.

name: Jus solis (art. 12,I,a)
description: The principle of acquiring nationality based on birth within a country's territory, as outlined in Article 12, Section I, Subsection a, of the Brazilian Nationality Law.

name: Jus sanguinis
description: The principle of acquiring nationality through descent from a national, regardless of the place of birth.

name: Definitiva (art. 12,I,b)
description: A characteristic of Brazilian nationality indicating its permanency and irrevocability, once granted, as per Article 12, Section I, Subsection b, of the Brazilian Nationality Law.

name: Suspensvel
description: A characteristic of Brazilian nationality implying its potential to be temporarily suspended under specific circumstances, as defined by Brazilian law.

name: Origem pas de lngua portuguesa
description: Originating from a country where Portuguese is the official language, a factor that can influence the process and requirements for acquiring Brazilian nationality.
